{
  "stem": "1765.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 96.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The dog tag I just mentioned before was found about three or four weeks after my father's-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I guess you would call it-- division went actually to the front lines.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And maybe it wasn't four weeks, maybe it was closer to three weeks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never thought about the time, but of course, we must know it, chronologically.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was in the beginning, say, in the middle of September.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the middle of October, my father came to Vilna as if he would really had risen from the dead.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the first stop he made was to my grandmother's, on my mother's side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Her name was Sonia Zunser.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was my mother's second mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother's birth mother died when my mother was three, and she was brought up by Sonia Zunser, who was a saint.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we'll talk about her later, I hope.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But my father went to her house first.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was my Uncle Liusik and Margola.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And apparently the first thing my grandmother Sonia said, 'I didn't make your favorite chicken.' And the story was that my father and all the soldiers in his unit were given permission to discard their dog-- their dog tags, is what they were called, and uniforms, and to make their way wherever they could, whichever way they could.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The colonel gave them leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he took off his uniform and remained in his-- and he had to take off his boots-- and he remained in his underwear, and he picked up a blanket, and a beret, and a safety pin, and a pair of shoes in bags that were left by people who were running east from the Germans.",
      "word_count": 56
    }
  ],
